- Download the zip file from coursera website
  Using 'download.file()' to download the file.
- unzip the file and store in the R_DATA folder
  Using 'unzip()' to unzip the zip file
- read/load the data to Rstudio
  Using read.table() to load the data to R
- merge the data from train file and test file separately after that combine both file together as fullData set.
  Using 'cbind()' to combine train,test data together and 'rbind()' both data set in 1.
- Extracts only the measurements on the mean and standard deviation for each measurement.
  Using 'grep()' function to find the indexes with "mean" and "std".
  select all relevant columns and set the columns name using the selected features name.
- Uses descriptive activity names to name the activities in the data set
  Using 'factor()' to replace the numbers to activity names.
- Make the fieldName/variable name more descriptive
  Using 'gsub()' to make the name more descriptive.
- Tidy data set with the average of each variable for each activity and each subject
  Using 'group_by()' and 'summarise_each()' for each activity and each subject.
